            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20truth%20in%20the%20saying%20%22All%20that%20glitters%20is%20not%20gold.%22%20First%20John%204%3A1%20warns%20us%20not%20to%20believe%20every%20spirit.%20Just%20as%20Satan%20can%20masquerade%20as%20an%20angel%20of%20light%2C%20so%20a%20person%20living%20for%20Satan%20can%20say%20the%20right%20words%20but%20live%20the%20wrong%20way.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESome%20false%20prophets%20speak%20very%20glibly%20and%20eloquently%20but%20oppose%20the%20very%20truth%20of%20God.%20Rejecting%20the%20fact%20that%20Jesus%20has%20come%20in%20the%20flesh%2C%20these%20prophets%20often%20refer%20to%20Him%20as%20a%20wonderful%20leader%20or%20a%20great%20teacher.%20In%20fact%2C%20most%20world%20religions%20recognize%20Christ%20as%20a%20great%20person.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20Holy%20Spirit%20will%20give%20you%20discernment%20and%20wisdom%20to%20spot%20indicators%20that%20are%20contrary%20to%20the%20Spirit%20of%20Jesus.%20Daniel%20said%2C%20%22Those%20who%20are%20wise%20will%20shine%20as%20bright%20as%20the%20sky%2C%20and%20those%20who%20turn%20many%20to%20righteousness%20will%20shine%20like%20stars%20forever%22%20(Daniel%2012%3A3).%20We%20must%20depend%20on%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%2C%20the%20One%20of%20whom%20John%20said%2C%20%22The%20Spirit%20who%20lives%20in%20you%20is%20greater%20than%20the%20spirit%20who%20lives%20in%20the%20world%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E(1%20John%204%3A4).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFollow%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20and%20godly%20pastoral%20authority.%20Be%20wise%20and%20discerning.%20Satan%20can't%20hide%20forever%2C%20and%20the%20Lord%20knows%20how%20to%20keep%20you%20out%20of%20the%20enemy's%20deceptive%20web.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
